<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hold the line against someone • hold the line at someone</xh5><p> <i>hold the line against someone—</i>take a firm opposing stand with regard to smb.: You’ve been <u>holding the line against</u> those who have sought to legislate the Second Amendment into oblivion.</p><p> <i>hold the line at someone—</i>preclude a person from being invited or admitted to a place: The Browns and the Smiths could be invited, but I think we ought to <u>hold the line at</u> the Browns.</p> </entry>
